    <contents> 
        <p>Crab Meat and <object><item ref="Scuttle">Scuttle</item></object></p>
        <p>2 handfuls of <object><item ref="Scuttle">Scuttle</item></object></p>
        <p>4 pinches of <object><item ref="wickwheat">wickwheat</item></object></p>
        <p>1 <object><item ref="large Kwama egg">large kwama egg</item></object></p>
        <p>the meat of one <person ref="mudcrab">mudcrab</person> (two portions)</p>
       <p> 1 handful of chopped <object><item ref="bittergreen">bittergreen</item></object></p>
        
        <p>Beat eggs, <object><item ref="wickwheat">wickwheat</item></object>, and <object><item ref="Scuttle">Scuttle</item></object> in a large bowl. Slowly stir in crabmeat and <object><item ref="bittergreen">bittergreen</item></object>. Bake covered in a hot over for one half hour to one hour (when a knife comes out clean).</p>
        
        <p>The Hound and Rat</p>
        <p>1 pie crust</p>
        <p>1 pound of ground meat (mixed <object><item ref="Rat Meat">rat</item></object> and <object><item ref="Nix-Hound Meat">hound</item></object>)</p>
        <p>a hand and a half of cooked <object><item ref="saltrice">saltrice</item></object></p>
        <p> 1 handful of <object><item ref="Scuttle">Scuttle</item></object></p>
        <p>1 small <object><item ref="Kwama egg">Kwama egg</item></object></p>
        <p>a pinch of <object><item ref="ash salts">ash salts</item></object></p>
        
        <p>Cook the mixed meat in a pan over an open flame. When the meat begins to brown, add the <object><item ref="saltrice">saltrice</item></object>. Stir for a few moments and add the <object><item ref="Scuttle">Scuttle</item></object> and <object><item ref="Kwama egg">Kwama egg</item></object>. When the <object><item ref="Kwama egg">Kwama egg</item></object> is fully cooked and the <object><item ref="Scuttle">Scuttle</item></object> has melted, pour from the pan into the pie crust. Sprinkle with <object><item ref="ash salts">ash salts</item></object> and cover the pie crust. Bake for one quarter hour in a hot oven.</p>
